707182f-b.text:
(1)
Van Sicklen Street, east side, north of Ave. V., showing the home of C. Lake from 1857-1873. This house was erected in 1820 on the site of another structure, said to have been built a century earlier. Some sources state this property to have been possessed by this family for over 200 years.
February 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, view eastward.
February 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, a view north from the Old Gravesend Cemetery. In the background is P.S. No. 95, at the N.E. corner of Neck Road and Van Sicklen Street.
February 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4)
The same, showing a northwest view. The house at the extreme right is No. 373 Van Sicklen Street.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
